included.title: UX Strategist and Researcher with Clutch

included.description:
While at Rosetta, I had the opportunity to work with a wide variety of clients to help improve the user experience of their web sites and applications.  

While I primarily focused on user research activities such as User / Usability Testing and Heuristic Evaluations, I also worked as an interaction designer.  In my role, I was able to:
 - Work closely with clients to provide actionable feedback about improving the user experience and conversion of their website
 - Mentor and train a team of talented user experience professionals 
 - Develop strategic methods and solutions to help clients accomplish user research and testing goals
 - Act as a subject matter expert to guide project team members about the user experience design process, especially with regards to user research 

I'd be happy to discuss this role, and some of my specific accomplishments.  Rosetta was a great place to work, and I am excited to have had the opportunity to work with such a strong team.
included.title: User Research Manager

included.description:
Precision Dialogue Marketing (formerly Metrics Marketing) is an analytics-driven database marketing and interactive firm. PDM leverages data management, analytic consulting, automated marketing, interactive services, and direct marketing execution to improve marketing ROI for clients.

I had great opportunities at Metrics and Precision Dialogue to help my clients with their research and customer experience projects - either stand-alone or integrating these needs within a larger redesign.  

I expanded on my past roles by:
- Incorporating email optimization, eye tracking studies, surveys and quantitative research, and other methodologies
- Continuing to lead user research and interaction design projects on-time, on-budget, and across additional industries, including B2B and Health Insurance
- Discussing user research and user experience methods and strategies with clients across industries, including speaking engagements at Usability Professional Associations chapters and informal evaluations at conferences
included.title: Research & Customer Experience Director

included.companyName: RSA, The Security Division of EMC (RSA Security)
included.description:
User Experience Designer in group focused on improving the usability of various security products - including enterprise software and consumer security products.  My role focused on leading the UXD for the fast-paced redesign of the Authentication Manager product - a web-based tool to assist system administrators in providing secure access to users through SecurID tokens.  

I designed, evaluated, iterated, and documented complex new features for web-based administration console applications.  One of those applications focused on putting a web-based interface on command line utilities. In addition, I developed basic prototypes for consumer-facing security products and rapidly iterating on the designs based on usability testing. And was a key figure in creating persona-based design process and prototyping persona templates.
included.title: User Experience Designer

included.summary:
I believe technology should be a tool applied to make lives easier. My goal is to help people and businesses see the benefits of having technology work for them, not forcing people to try to adapt to machines but making machines fit human lives. I hope that soon we won't see technology in terms of what it can do, but in terms of what it can do for us. 

My passion, work experiences, and educational background compliment each other and put me in a unique postion to make a difference.

Specialties: Human-Computer Interaction, User Experience Design, User Research, Contextual Inquiry, Task Analysis, Heuristic Evaluation, Think-Aloud Usability Testing, User Centered Design,  Interaction Design, Prototyping, Eye Tracking, Email Optimization, In-Depth Interviews, and more.
included.headline: User Experience Researcher
